## ğŸ‘¥ Team Members and Their Roles

Each member contributed equally and significantly by taking responsibility for a designated section of the project and documentation.

### 1. Tamirat Dereje ([GitHub: @tamed29](https://github.com/tamed29))
**Role**: Game Engine and UI Integration  
**Key Contributions**:
- Developed the core game loop (`showMainMenu`, `playSinglePlayer`, `playMultiPlayer`).
- Implemented the user interface display using ANSI color codes.
- Managed full game integration and testing.
- create file that expliain member contributions.
### 2. Fuad Kedir ([GitHub: @furoyal7](https://github.com/furoyal7))
**Role**: Game Input Handling and Board Logic  
**Key Contributions**:
- Designed the input validation system and mapped positions to board cells.
- Developed and tested board rendering with dynamic number hints.
- Handled player move logic and error correction flow.

### 3. Pineal Tadesse ([GitHub: @Pomi-7](https://github.com/Pomi-7))
**Role**: AI Algorithms  
**Key Contributions**:
- Implemented the **Minimax algorithm** with alpha-beta pruning for hard AI.
- Developed and debugged the easy-mode random AI.
- Ensured smart decision-making for the computer player.

### 4. Beniyas Dawit ([GitHub: @Benas12-dv](https://github.com/Benas12-dv))
**Role**: Game State & Rule Engine  
**Key Contributions**:
- Implemented the `checkWin`, `isBoardFull`, and `switchPlayer` logic.
- Tested win/draw conditions and fixed edge-case bugs.
- Added match replay functionality.

### 5. Ahmed Hussen ([GitHub: @Ahmeddin](https://github.com/Ahmeddin))
**Role**: Project Documentation and Changelog Manager  
**Key Contributions**:
- Drafted and structured the full `README.md` (parts 5 and 6).
- Created `Known Issues`, `Changelog`, and `Future Enhancements` sections.
- Managed versioning and improvement logs.

### 6. Yohannis Dereje ([GitHub: @Yohannis-10](https://github.com/Yohannis-10))
**Role**: Summary, Review, and Quality Control  
**Key Contributions**:
- Authored the `README.md` summary section with feature highlights.
- Reviewed and approved final code structure and documentation.
- Coordinated merging of all parts into one final deliverable.

